    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhile working on [reproducible builds](https://reproducible-builds.org/) for [openSUSE](https://en.opensuse.org/openSUSE:Reproducible_Builds), I found that\nour `neovim-0.10.4` fails one test when running after 2038-01-19\n\nYou can find the full test log at\nhttps://rb.zq1.de/other/neovim-FTBFS2038-log.txt\n\n```\nFailures:\n        From test_recover.vim:\n        Found errors in Test_recover_unmodified_file():\n        Caught exception in Test_recover_unmodified_file(): Vim(recover):E308: Warning: Original file may have been changed @ command line..script /home/abuild/rpmbuild/BUILD/neovim-0.10.4/test/old/testdir/runtest.vim[543]..function RunTheTest[55]..Test_recover_unmodified_file, line 8\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nIn Debian and openSUSE, one can reproduce it with\n```bash\nosc checkout openSUSE:Factory/neovim && cd $_\nosc build --noservice --clean --vm-type=kvm --build-opt=--vm-custom-opt=-rtc\\ base=2038-01-20T00:00:00\n```\n\nOr you use `date --set=2038-01-20` \nMaybe libfaketime can also do the trick.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTests should keep working for at least 15 years.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nopenSUSE-Tumbleweed 20250211\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nNA\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nNA\n\n### Installation\n\nopenSUSE/tarball-source",
